================================
=== OMP Custom Block Manager Plugin
=== Version: 1.0
=== Author: Juan Pablo Alperin <pkp@alperin.ca>
=== Co-Author: Bozana Bokan <bozana.bokan@cedis.fu-berlin.de>
================================

About
-----
This plugin is intended to enable users to create customizable HTML blocks for the sidebars.

License
-------
This plugin is licensed under the GNU General Public License v2. See the file COPYING for the complete terms of this license.

System Requirements
-------------------
Same requirements as the OMP 1.1 core.

Installation
------------
To install the plugin:
 - copy the plugin tar.gz file to your OMP/plugins/generic directory
 - to unzip the plugin inside the plugins/generic directory:
    $ tar xvzf customBlockManager-1.1.tar.gz 
 - from your OMP directory execute:
    $ php tools/upgrade.php upgrade
 - enable the plugin by going to:  Management > Website Settings > Plugins > Generic Plugins and selecting "ENABLE" under "Custom Block Manager Plugin"

Management
------------
The Plugin management interface can be found at Management > Website Settings > Plugins > Generic Plugins > Custom Block Manager. Once the plugin is enabled, blocks can be added, edited and deleted through this interface, using the function " Manage Custom Blocks".
NOTE: The added custom blocks will per default appear in the right sidebar, but this can be changed in Management > Website Settings > Appereance > Press Layout > Sidebar Management.


